ality.","test_description":"Run service path with controlled primary/fallback strings, assert expected character-level edit distance value, and verify metric record is persisted with correct correlation fields.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.2,"Integration":0.68,"System":0.07,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.02}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When both translators are available, the service returns the primary translation and logs the quality comparison in the background.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is orchestration across modules plus async side effect: response prioritization (primary) and background metric logging. Real infrastructure is not strictly required; deterministic stubs for both translators can expose race/order bugs and missing background dispatch. INTEGRATION-BRAKE: (a) no required real OS/network/subprocess in behavior text, (b) correctness target is routing/background side effect, not model quality itself, (c) not a multi-agentic pipeline. Rejected Workflow because behavior text describes one request flow with one background comparison step, not multiple agentic stages whose outputs feed later model steps.","test_description":"With both translators stubbed as available, invoke service and assert immediate response equals primary output; then await/observe async worker or queue and assert quality comparison log/metric is emitted and persisted.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.06,"Integration":0.74,"System":0.12,"Agentic":0.05,"Workflow":0.03}}]}
